I don't think I'm alone in stating that 2022 was a rather transformative year. One cannot pass through life without enduring both hardships and victories... and with all that transpired, 2022 ended on a victorious note! ✨

My photography career has kept me very busy; I cannot begin to express my gratitude and appreciation for all of the incredible people who had allowed me to make art with them (and those who had invited me into their lives and left a lasting impact on mine). ✨

From photo shoots to explorations, festivals to tradeshows, I traveled the country more than I ever have before, experiencing countless adventures along the way! ✨

I had a wonderful time with @sigmaphoto and @samys_camera, putting together so many amazing workshops - and I am excited for what there is in store next year. ✨

My loved ones went through so many beautiful life chapters, from marriage to starting families, and it's been such a joy to be able to experience all of that with them. With the gloom of the past couple of years, this was the shining light we all needed! ✨

2023 is already gearing up to be yet another big adventure, with several announcements coming in the next few weeks ✨

It's impossible to include all of my favorite sessions from 2022 in just 20 images (there would be a carousel of hundreds of images if I had my way!), so here is just a quick sampling of some of the photographic endeavors 2022 had in store. ✨

May you all have a wonderful New Year's Eve and a fantastic 2023!

My favorite part of what I do is the people I meet. When @adventure_our_life reached out to me, I immediately knew she was someone who would leave a lasting impression on me. 🦋

Amy got in touch with me through social media, wanting to book a photo session with her Australian shepherd @miss_roxy_emilia as a surprise gift for her husband. 

Additionally, she wanted to capture a few images to talk about her story and bring awareness to a conversation that needs to be had: melanoma. 

Amy is a 3-time melanoma survivor, having started her journey at the young age of 27. Her story continues, with a goal of bringing more awareness to all about the importance of protecting your skin from the sun (and getting your skin checked by your dermatologist). 

This was an amazing experience; to meet such a sweet, vibrant, and loving woman whose beautiful outlook on life remains unchanged despite all that she had been through. Her dog was equally as precious, with an exuberant love for life! 

For those in the Las Vegas area, Amy has started a team benefiting the American Melanoma Institute that will be hosting a 5K run / walk on May 6th. You can donate, purchase tickets, and learn more at https://givebutter.com/c/AMI5k/members/ButterflyWarriors ♥️

Every year I struggle picking just 10 photos from the past 12 months to share. This year, the struggle was even worse - I still can't quite narrow it down and I haven't even scratched the surface of all that has been captured this year. 

2023 was an adventurous one, filled with constant national and international travel, exploring places I had never been, capturing some incredible moments on camera, and teaching on larger platforms than ever before. All of this inspired so much creativity in my work. 

There aren't strong enough words in either of the languages I know to express my gratitude to continue to be able to do what I love most. My photography business celebrated 14 years in 2023, a number that almost doesn't seem real! 

With every fiber of my being... Thank you. Thank you for letting me share my passions. Thank you to all who found themselves in front of my lens, all who sat through my photography lectures and participated in my workshops, and an immense thank you to all those that enjoy my photos. 

I cannot wait to see what 2024 brings!
